## When to use this component

Breadcrumbs are a form of navigation to convey the hierarchical relationship between pages, the analogy of parent > child > grand child is often used to describe this. 

They are used, not only as a form of navigation but for orientation. If a user was to arrive on a “child” page they should be able to understand where they currently are in the hierarchy of the website.

### When not to use this component

Breadcrumbs are not appropriate for use in a flat website structure or to convey progress. We recommend using [back button](/design-patterns/patterns/components/back_button/) links as part of a linear journey or transaction.

Their use should also be considered against other navigational devices on the page. Breadcrumbs will not be necessary where there is permanently visible navigation, such as a sidebar.

