### Mobile varient example (Alpha)

When displayed on a mobile some of the visual relationship between pages in the breadcrumb are lost due to content wrapping over multiple lines. It also pushes the main content further down the page.

This component has a CSS modifier to collapse the breadcrumb into a single link, similar to the [back button](/design-patterns/patterns/components/back_button/). 

This reveals the parent of the current page so the user can travel up through the hierarchy of the site or section.



